```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['year', 'people']]
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['people'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=19, color='green', alpha=0.75)
    plt.axvline(data['age'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the population?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('sex').sum()
    ax = data.plot(kind='bar', rot=0, legend=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('Sex')
    ax.set_ylabel('Population')
    ax.set_title('What is the gender distribution of the population?')
    ax.axhline(y=data['people'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['age', 'sex'])['people'].sum().reset_index()
    male_data = data[data['sex'] == 1]
    female_data = data[data['sex'] == 2]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(male_data['age'], male_data['people'], color='b', label='Male')
    ax.bar(female_data['age'], female_data['people'], bottom=male_data['people'], color='r', label='Female')
    ax.set_xlabel('Age')
    ax.set_ylabel('Population')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of population across different age groups?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.pivot('age', 'year', 'people')
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
    sns.heatmap(data, cmap='YlGnBu')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different years and age groups?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Age')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
